<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54105f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54105f">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54105f"> 105(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Zaid (son)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Another early believer was <mark>Zaid</mark>, who had been Mohammed&apos;s slave, and whom he had freed and <mark>adopted as a son</mark>. When Zaid was a young child he had fallen into the hands of some wandering Arabs, who had carried him off and sold him as a slave, and it so happened that he was given to Khad&#299;jah soon after her marriage with Mohammed. <small> Edith Holland, <a name="EHSM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EHSM"><cite title="source">The Story of Mohammed</cite></a> (1914) 46</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
